# Coding Guidelines

## Code Standards before Commiting:

•	Readability and Consistency:
o	Code easy to read and uses a consistent coding style.
o	Variable and function names make sense with what they perform.
•	Comments and Documentation:
o	Comments to explain code and documentation (README).
•	Functionality and Requirements:
o	Check that code functions properly according to the requirements in the specifications.
•	Error Handling:
o	Properly handle errors and exceptions
o	Log errors and display error messages.
•	Testing:
o	Verify that code has appropriate unit tests and has proper coverage, negative and positive.
•	Code Organization:
o	Check that code is organized into logical modules and class
o	Check the functions are manageable and broken
